                     <interp inst="t18050918-102-person936" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , he is a <rs id="t18050918-102-viclabel547" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18050918-102-victim933 t18050918-102-viclabel547"></join>, <placeName id="t18050918-102-crimeloc548">No. 363, Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18050918-102-crimeloc548" type="placeName" value="No. 363, Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18050918-102-crimeloc548" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18050918-102-off545 t18050918-102-crimeloc548"></join>.</p>
               <p>Q. Do you remember the last witness, Lane, bringing any man into your shop? - A. Yes, he brought the prisoner at the bar into the shop and the calico; the calico is Mr. Richards's property, I know it by the mark and the pattern; I had seen it there ten minutes before I missed it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18050918-102-person937">
                  SARAH 
                  FERM
               <interp inst="t18050918-102-person937" type="surname" value="FERM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18050918-102-person937" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18050918-102-person937" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - Q. Do you recollect seeing the prisoner on this day they are speaking of? - A. Yes, I was looking out of the garret window of the house, I saw the prisoner take this yellow piece of calico, and put it under his apron.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I never stood near that yellow piece, I only took the other piece to look at, and that man came and took me by the arm, and pulled me away; I turned back, and put the piece on the bench; I asked him what he did that for; he told me in fun, and the other man came and took hold of me, and said I took it; I looked at the other bit, and meant to buy it if I could, to make a gown for my wife, but the yellow piece I never touched it, if I am to die this minute.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18050918-102-verdict549" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18050918-102-verdict549" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>, aged 72.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18050918-102-punish550" type="punishmentDescription">
